
# VPN_SWITCH_CREDENTIALS_openvpn - Path to OpenVPN credentials file
#
# Optional credential file for automated OpenVPN authentication.
# This follows the VPN_SWITCH_CREDENTIALS_<protocol> naming convention for
# protocol-agnostic credential lookup.
#
# Default: (empty - interactive authentication)
#
# If set, vpn-switch will automatically patch OpenVPN configs to use this
# credentials file for authentication. The file should contain exactly 2 lines:
#   Line 1: username (e.g., username+provider)
#   Line 2: password
#
# Example:
#   /home/user/.vpn/credentials.txt
#
# Format:
#   - Must be an absolute path
#   - File should have 0600 permissions (readable only by owner)
#   - vpn-switch will NOT create or manage this file
#
# Behavior:
#   - If this variable is set: auth-user-pass directives are patched to use this file
#   - If this variable is NOT set: interactive authentication prompt (default behavior)
#   - Configs with existing auth-user-pass paths are left unchanged
#
# Security:
#   - Keep credentials file outside VPN database directory
#   - Never commit credentials to version control
#   - Use restrictive permissions (chmod 0600)
